<h1>Problem 130 - 2016 Balkan MO SL, N5       , N</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 7</h2>
<p>A positive integer is called downhill if the digits in its decimal representation form a nonstrictly decreasing sequence from left to right. Suppose that a polynomial \(P(x)\) with rational coefficients takes on an integer value for each downhill positive integer \(x\). Is it necessarily true that \(P(x)\) takes on an integer value for each integer \(x\)?</p>
